	(134,1,'2013-10-16 02:23:39','2013-10-16 02:23:39','Matthew facilitates the successful execution of Projects as AGD\'s COO and Director of Project Management.  His areas of expertise are: Product Management, Product Marketing, Project Management, Operations Management, Strategic Planning &amp; Execution, Operational Excellence, Change Management, Product/Process Transfer, Human Capital Management, Training &amp; Development.\r\n\r\nHe takes on a variety of Project Management Consulting roles with our clients (both startup and well established companies), focusing on new product development and technologies for desktop/web/mobile/cloud based applications.\r\n\r\nThe Technical Stuff:\r\nApplication Project Management, Agile/Scrum Methodology, Stage-Gate, Waterfall, MS Office, Microsoft Project, Adobe CS6, Crystal Reports, Salesforce, UX Technical Documentation... and a bunch of SaaS Applications.','Matthew Santos','','publish','closed','closed','','matt-santos','','','2014-08-05 07:39:00','2014-08-05 07:39:00','',0,'http://ag.dev/dev/?post_type=team&#038;p=134',1,'team','',0),
	(135,1,'2013-10-16 02:29:26','2013-10-16 02:29:26','Perlita adds a flare to the AG Design team. Poised, articulate and with a penchant for dry humor, Perlita keeps the joy de vivre at AGD.\r\n\r\nPerlita is responsible for overseeing project direction. She adeptly manages client expectations and direction, and the design team’s vision. Perlita is often responsible for coordinating project production. Her writing savvy has aided many clients with developing copy, press releases, and editing.\r\n\r\nWhen she is not fiddling with words, Perlita enjoys cooking, wine tasting, camping, going to sporting events and spending time with her family.\r\n\r\nThe Technical Stuff:\r\nMS Office, Microsoft Project, Adobe CS6, Social Media, PR, Content Management Systems (Drupal, Joomla, Wordpress, Apostrophe, Concrete5), CMS Trainings &amp; User Documentation Manuals... Making sure clients LOVE us!','Perlita Herrera','','draft','closed','closed','','perlita-herrera','','','2014-09-26 20:26:21','2014-09-26 20:26:21','',0,'http://ag.dev/dev/?post_type=team&#038;p=135',3,'team','',0),
	(136,1,'2013-10-16 02:30:22','2013-10-16 02:30:22','Jennifer wins the office trophy of Most Outgoing. Her laugh is infectious. With little direction, Jennifer, or Jenn, as she likes to be called, is able to develop a simple concept into a visual masterpiece.\r\n\r\nJennifer’s love for design was fostered at an early age. Her talent has been crafted by years of experience. While her love affair began with print design, Jennifer’s skills spans the spectrum of media.\r\n\r\nWhen Jennifer isn’t pairing beautiful typography with vivid imagery, Jennifer explores the Bay Area in search of good eats, antique and thrift store treasures, and scenic running trails.\r\n\r\nThe Technical Stuff:\r\nAdobe CS6, MS Office, iOS/Android Mobile App Design, UI Specification &amp; UX Flow Documentation… mounting mocks and on black boards the old school way.','Jennifer Vaughn','','publish','closed','closed','','jennifer-vaughn','','','2013-11-21 16:48:08','2013-11-21 16:48:08','',0,'http://ag.dev/dev/?post_type=team&#038;p=136',4,'team','',0),
	(138,1,'2013-10-16 02:31:23','2013-10-16 02:31:23','Chelsey has a passion for creating beautiful, yet intuitive websites.  She is especially keen on learning, exploring, and figuring out new CMS platforms like Wordpress. Chelsey assists in creating assets for web based applications and supporting our print design.  She\'s also designed and coded a few client websites utilizing Wordpress as the CMS platform.\r\n\r\nThe Technical Stuff:\r\nAdobe CS6, MS Office, Responsive/Mobile/Tablet Design, Application Design, HTML, Wordpress','Chelsey Johnson','','publish','closed','closed','','chelsey-johnson','','','2014-08-05 07:07:34','2014-08-05 07:07:34','',0,'http://ag.dev/dev/?post_type=team&#038;p=138',7,'team','',0),
	(139,1,'2013-10-16 02:31:58','2013-10-16 02:31:58','Resident acronym handler. Crafting a better looking internet with HTML5, CSS, and JS. Currently specializing in RWD.\r\n\r\nMatt…aka, the other Matt, is our Lead Developer. He is passionate about his work and is dedicated to innovation and creating world class products that will delight customers. He\'s familiar with full product development cycle and is responsible for developing the top commercial quality UI components of Products in Web as well as Mobile space.\r\n\r\nHe collaborates effectively with UX Design, Engineering and Product Management teams to develop a world class eCommerce user experience products, creates UI development best practices within engineering departments, rapidly prototypes interfaces, performs design and code review UI deliverables, and extensive tests cross browser compatibility (FireFox, Chrome, Safari, IE 9/10… and the dreaded and soon to be retired IE8)\r\n\r\nThe Technical Stuff:\r\nJavascript/jQuery, CSS 3, XHTML, HTML5, AJAX, XML, JSON, DOM, PHP, Wordpress, Drupal, Apostrophe, Code Ignitor, Symfony, MySQL, Web Server Technology, Server Site Programming and Web Service (SOAP, REST) integration practices… need we say more?','Matt Rust','','publish','closed','closed','','matt-rust','','','2013-11-16 00:30:42','2013-11-16 00:30:42','',0,'http://ag.dev/dev/?post_type=team&#038;p=139',8,'team','',0),
	(140,1,'2013-10-16 02:32:24','2013-10-16 02:32:24','Having worked in a wide range of places, including circuses, the South Pole and a nuclear reactor, Tyler is now our backend developer and technical ninja. He has experience in PHP using Symfony, JavaScript using Node.js, Ruby, Java, C++ and Server Configuration. He enjoys researching and learning to use new, cutting edge technologies and clever implementations.\r\n\r\nThe Technical Stuff:\r\nPHP, Symfony, JavaScript using Node.js, Ruby, Java, C++ and Server Configuration, CSS 3, XHTML, HTML5, AJAX, XML, JSON, mySQL','Tyler Freeman','','publish','closed','closed','','tyler-freeman','','','2013-10-20 08:15:12','2013-10-20 08:15:12','',0,'http://ag.dev/dev/?post_type=team&#038;p=140',9,'team','',0),
	(141,1,'2013-10-16 02:32:40','2013-10-16 02:32:40','Eliot has almost 30 years of industry experience, including extensive knowledge of a variety of operating systems and programming languages.\r\n\r\nHe has a B.S. (with Highest Honors) in EECS, UC Berkeley; M.S. in Computer Graphics, UC Berkeley; and extensive experience in 3D graphics including Maya and AutoStudio.\r\n\r\nHe\'s familiar with full product development cycle and is responsible for developing the top commercial quality UI components of Products in Web as well as Mobile space.\r\n\r\nThe Technical Stuff:\r\nUnix (SunOS, IRIX, Linux, BSD), Windows, C, C++, Perl, CGI, HTML, tcl, SQL, Joomla, Wordpress, Drupal, Custom CMS, PHP, Python, Javascript, Flash, HTML5, Photoshop, DHTML… this list is just getting warmed up.','Eliot','','publish','closed','closed','','eliot','','','2013-11-16 00:31:01','2013-11-16 00:31:01','',0,'http://ag.dev/dev/?post_type=team&#038;p=141',10,'team','',0),
