	(167,2,'2013-10-23 23:02:41','2013-10-23 23:02:41','Matthew facilitates the successful execution of Projects as AGD\'s COO and DirectProject Manager.  His areas of expertise are: Product Management, Product Marketing, Project Management, Operations Management, Strategic Planning &amp; Execution, Operational Excellence, Change Management, Product/Process Transfer, Human Capital Management, Training &amp; Development.\n\nHe takes on a variety of Project Management Consulting roles with our clients (both startup and well established companies), focusing on new product development and technologies for desktop/web/mobile/cloud based applications.\n\nThe Technical Stuff:\nApplication Project Management, Agile/Scrum Methodology, Stage-Gate, Waterfall, MS Office, Microsoft Project, Adobe CS6, Crystal Reports, Salesforce, UX Technical Documentation... and a bunch of SaaS Applications.','Matthew Santos','','inherit','open','open','','134-autosave-v1','','','2013-10-23 23:02:41','2013-10-23 23:02:41','',134,'http://ag.dev/dev/?p=167',0,'revision','',0),
	(168,2,'2013-10-31 22:28:03','2013-10-31 22:28:03','Arlene Santos brings over a decade of creative design and strategic marketing experience. She provides key strategic vision and leadership across cross-disciplinary development and oversees the successful execution of all creative strategies. Arlene has the unique ability to interpret her clients\' communications strategies and develop creative approaches and treatments that align with that strategy. Arlene routinely leads projects and campaigns in cross matrix reporting environments, often advising VP and CXO level management in the areas of innovation, user-engagement, brand recognition and optimization. Arlene has lead teams that have designed and executed hundreds of UI/UX design/development projects, collecting award-winning results along the way.\n\nArlene received two Bachelor of Fine Arts (BFA) degrees in Graphic Design from the University of San Francisco (USF) and California College of the Arts (CCA), graduating Magna-Cum-Laude. Arlene began freelance consulting, building her clientele since 2001 and has grown AGD into a prominent UI/UX consultancy sought-out by clients such as Hitachi, Western Digital, Johnson &amp; Johnson.\n\nArlene is well received by her clients and bases her success on the success of each client and the results they achieve. She has created long lasting relationships with clients that lead to ongoing projects and campaigns. She contributes her success to her design process, strong work ethic, and dedication to projects.\n\nArlene actively participates in her community and sits on the board of directors for Mt. Diablo Business Women and serves as the co-chair for Women In Consulting, East Bay.','Arlene Santos','','inherit','open','open','','55-autosave-v1','','','2013-10-31 22:28:03','2013-10-31 22:28:03','',55,'http://ag.dev/dev/?p=168',0,'revision','',0),
